transcript.text: Hello, welcome to the on Print shop.
In this video we will walk you through the enhancements we have made to the master product options in this release.
In version 11.2 we introduce stock management for product options, enhanced the pricing structure and added a new option type text area.
Let us walk you through these enhancements 1 by 1, talking about the new stock management functionality.
First, you can now add and manage stocks for product options in the system.
Earlier, there was no provision to help admins manage their stocks of physical items such as product options.
They had to manually place the orders when the stock was not available.
We are introducing the stock management functionality on the master product option level.
The admin can find the Manage Stock button on the Product Options listing page in the top right corner from the Add or Edit page.
The admin can now maintain common stock or inventory across all the products that are using the same stock of product option.
The stock can be managed with any of these three options, option wise, attribute wise, and option combination wise.
In the option wise, users can set a common stock quantity for master options and specify multipliers for individual attributes.
For example, if stock is configured for grommets, enter multipliers 2 for two corner, 4 for four corner to deduct the respective quantities based on attribute selection.
If you don't want to deduct quantity for a specific attribute, leave the multiplier field blank.
In the attribute wise.
The admin can manage stock for each attribute individually.
For example, assign 5000 units for a cross base banner stand and 1000 units for a square base banner stand.
Whereas in the option Combination wise, the admin can manage stock for various attribute combinations.
For instance, you can set stock levels for combinations like 1000 units for a small red full sleeve T-shirt and 2000 units for a medium red full sleeve T-shirt.
The admin can also manage the notification when the product stock reaches a certain point with the stock setting button.
This screen will allow the admin to enable the notify me when the stock is reached at and allow order if the the product is out of stock.
For individual product options, the history button at the top right corner shows a pop up with all the product stock history.
Here admin can filter the stock data for a specific time span.
Instead of crediting and debiting stock for each product, the admin can import the stock with an excel file.
The next enhancement is the changes in the pricing.
The admins will now have the provision to add attribute level multiplier even in formula based pricing on the assigned product screen.
The option level multiplier for individual attributes, common multiplier and setup cost can now be overridden for any specific product.
Talking about another change in the product options, the admin can now create a text area type of product master options as well.
So these were some enhancements we brought in the product options.
If you have any questions, our support executives are here to help.
Just reach out through live chat on on printshop.
Com Thanks for tuning in.
